commitResults.messageTitle: Add capture for up/down keystrokes in CommandBox

commitResults.messageBody:
Created a new class CommandHistory to store previous commands and
modified CommandBox to store successfully executed commands in the
history.

When entering a command, the up and down arrow keys can be used to view
previously entered commands. Additionally, any change to a command is
saved when navigating to another command, so that the user is able to
navigate to a previous command to refer to it, and return back to their
new command to finish it.
Add command history

commitResults.messageBody:
- Team list added to GUI beside the contact list
- The minimum window size has been increased to ensure that all UI
  components are not clipped.

  contact/team list) now expand to fill the available space instead
  of having a fixed width/height
- Contact's tags/techstack will now overflow to a second row instead
  being truncated by the contact card's width
- Font sizes for command input and result window have been increased
  for better readability.

person in the address book. The feature ensures that usernames

GitHub's username requirements.

Unit tests have been added to validate the functionality and robustness
of the new feature.
